Covid-19 Pandemic Impact on Bikeshare at Boston¶

by Hassan¶

Introduction¶

Coronavirus has had a large-scale impact on transportation. This study attempts to assess the effects of COVID-19 on biking. Bikeshare data was used to understand the impacts of COVID-19 during the initial wave of the disease on biking in Boston

The study period was split into two phases—no COVID-19 phase at the secound quarted of 2019, cases increasing phase at the secound quarter of 2020.

The Original data extracted from https://www.bluebikes.com/system-data

Preliminary Wrangling¶


Dataset cover the Bikeshare data in Boston in two duration
secound Quarter of 2019 (April , May and June ) before Covid-19
and the secound Quarter of 2020 (April , May and June ) during Covid-19


Dataset Original structural is as follow :
Trip Duration (seconds)
Start Time and Date
Stop Time and Date
Start Station Name & ID
End Station Name & ID
Bike ID
User Type (Casual = Single Trip or Day Pass user; Member = Annual or Monthly Member)
Birth Year
Gender, self-reported by member (Zero=unknown; 1=male; 2=female)

Data Wrangling¶



  1. Gather the data from the website and create two data frames for each period (2Q of 2019 & 2Q of 2020)
  2. Drop un needed columns
  3. Convert start time and stop time to Datetime type
  4. Extract (Month , Day of week and Hour) from start time column
  5. Check for duplicates
  6. Check for Null values
  7. Replace the "other" in gender with male or female based on the original porpotion
  8. fill the null values in gender and birth date with the same porpotion of the original data
  9. Create a new column for each period
  10. Creat a trip column form start station and end station
  11. Combine the two datasets in df to start the Exploration phase

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset showing the information of bike share trips in Boston in two period of times
(secound quarter of 2019 and secound quareter of 2020)
consist of 14 column covering ( trip duration , trip distination , number of trips and user information)
distibuted in 1,026,065 rows
tripduration - quantitative continuous variable
the remaining columns are categorical nominal variable
('start station name','end station name', 'bikeid', 'usertype', 'birth year', 'gender','month', 'day', 'hour', 'year', 'Trip')

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

Total number of trips variables before and during the pandemic
and features effecting trips duration

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

user information (gender , user type , birth year)
Trip information (start station , trip)

# compute the logarithm of price to make multivariate plotting easier
def log_trans(x, inverse = False):
    """ quick function for computing log and power operations """
    if not inverse:
        return np.log10(x)
    else:
        return np.power(10, x)

df['log_tripduration'] = df['tripduration'].apply(log_trans)
